message: Two opposing perspectives are in the lede. That is fair.
Removed reference to dikotters work which is polemical and has not been academically reiewed. Dikotter has made racist and extremist comments on Chinese in the past.
Removing references to Dikotters work, only recently released and not yet academically reviewed. Furthermore Dikotter's book is clearly of an extreme polemical nature.
saying that the CR was simply an act of vengeance by Mao is treating a very complex movement in an over simplistic way - just pure speculation; Remember - no mind reading.
/* Misrepresentation of famine image on book cover */
Dikotter's misrepresentation deserves a separate section. Because it indicates intellectual dishonesty, and racism.
(Mr Griffin - the same could be said of polemical reactionary sources. The lede has two reactionary sources, two non-reactionary sources. That is fair.)
its good to separate Mishras review, as it is slightly different from the others. There is no need to talk of the cover for the American edition - it does not relate to the heading of the section.
